sec.p:
A logarithmic scale of base 10 was used to express mean neutralizing antibody titers. Statistically significant differences were assessed using the Shapiro–Wilk and the non-parametric Wilcoxon-Mann–Whitney tests. The comparison was made between:
Neutralizing antibodies (NAs) against BuAHV-1 between vaccination groups (VAX-1 and VAX-2) and control groups (CNT);
NAs against BoAHV-1 between vaccination groups (VAX-1 and VAX-2) and control groups (CNT).
